      "writtenOn": "2021-07-13T21:09:18Z",
      "side": 0,
      "message": "I don\u0027t like SkScalarNearlyEqual here because it\u0027s a fixed cutoff that doesn\u0027t consider the view matrix. A very small oval with a view matrix that blows it up to screen size would draw wrong.\n\nI\u0027d just as soon use \u003d\u003d, but if not, I think we\u0027d have to check if the device width and height are nearly equal, not the oval-space width and height.\n\nThoughts?",
      "parentUuid": "f784fd07_1e0c24e3",
